Erasure Coding
    Instead of just copying data (like replication), it:
    
    Splits data into pieces
    Adds extra “parity” pieces
    So even if some pieces are lost, you can still reconstruct the original data
    
    
    - Less storage overhead than replication
    - High durability
    
    - More CPU cost to encode/decode
    - Slightly slower recovery
    
    - used HDFS, S3
        
